  "body": "In the https://github.com/ethereum/tests/blob/v7.0.0/BlockchainTests/ValidBlocks/VMTests/vmSha3Test/sha3_memSizeNoQuadraticCost31.json test\r\n\r\nthe initial balance is\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/tests/blob/5e4539b1b50747e699a5990b3f8696c9267e6c31/BlockchainTests/ValidBlocks/VMTests/vmSha3Test/sha3_memSizeNoQuadraticCost31.json#L15\r\n\r\nand after sending `0x7c`, the final balance is \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/tests/blob/5e4539b1b50747e699a5990b3f8696c9267e6c31/BlockchainTests/ValidBlocks/VMTests/vmSha3Test/sha3_memSizeNoQuadraticCost31.json#L106\r\n\r\nIs this the expected way to manage overflows? I think that will have more sense to do saturating overflow or just reject the tx.\r\n\r\n(since is filled by geth, cc/@karalabe)",
